964
01:39:36,815 --> 01:39:39,613
No, but I'm over here.
Can't you see me?

965
01:39:39,718 --> 01:39:43,711
Listen, sweetheart, if I could see you,
I wouldn't be working here.

966
01:39:43,822 --> 01:39:47,121
Well, what do you see?

967
01:39:47,225 --> 01:39:49,193
I see what you see.

968
01:39:49,294 --> 01:39:54,095
Nurse Bibs.
Nurse Bibs and a rubber horse.

969
01:39:54,199 --> 01:39:57,100
Oh. Oh, I see.

970
01:39:57,202 --> 01:40:00,968
Th-Thank you, Nurse Bibs.

971
01:40:01,072 --> 01:40:02,972
Thank you.

972
01:41:12,377 --> 01:41:15,505
<i>Hi.</i>

973
01:41:18,183 --> 01:41:20,151
<i>Are you out there?</i>

974
01:41:21,886 --> 01:41:26,346
<i>Well, I see your light's still on,</i>
<i>so I guess you must be out there.</i>

975
01:41:26,458 --> 01:41:28,358
<i>Hmm?</i>

976
01:41:30,895 --> 01:41:33,864
<i>It’s okay if you don't wanna talk, you know.</i>

977
01:41:33,965 --> 01:41:36,991
<i>I don't wanna talk either sometimes.</i>

978
01:41:37,102 --> 01:41:40,071
<i>I just like to stay silent.</i>

979
01:41:46,911 --> 01:41:49,379
<i>Do you mind if I sit down?</i>

980
01:41:58,356 --> 01:42:00,881
Do you mind if I sit down?

981
01:42:03,361 --> 01:42:05,829
<i>No.</i>

982
01:42:07,599 --> 01:42:09,499
Thanks.

983
01:42:09,601 --> 01:42:14,163
My legs get a little tired
from standing all the time.

984
01:42:16,741 --> 01:42:19,938
Is this your first visit here?

985
01:42:20,044 --> 01:42:24,344
<i>- Yes.</i>
- Oh!

986
01:42:24,449 --> 01:42:28,215
Well, this whole thing
must seem kind of strange to you, huh?

987
01:42:28,319 --> 01:42:32,119
You realize that I can't see you
even though you can see me?

988
01:42:32,223 --> 01:42:36,023
Well, that takes a little gettin' used to.

989
01:42:36,127 --> 01:42:38,027
Oh.

990
01:42:38,129 --> 01:42:41,587
<i>Am I--Am I looking at your face now?</i>

991
01:42:50,041 --> 01:42:53,010
<i>Oh, God. It don't matter.</i>

992
01:42:53,111 --> 01:42:55,875
<i>Oh.</i>

993
01:43:05,990 --> 01:43:08,220
If, um --

994
01:43:08,326 --> 01:43:11,591
If there's anything you wanna talk about,
I'll just listen.

995
01:43:11,696 --> 01:43:13,596
All right?

996
01:43:13,698 --> 01:43:17,156
<i>I’m a real good listener.</i>

997
01:43:30,014 --> 01:43:32,710
Is there somethin' --

998
01:43:32,817 --> 01:43:36,480
I don't know.
Is there somethin' I can do for you?

999
01:43:45,230 --> 01:43:48,199
Do you mind if I take off my sweater?

1000
01:43:49,934 --> 01:43:52,061
I'll just take off my sweater.

1001
01:43:52,170 --> 01:43:54,695
<i>No, no. No. Don't.</i>

1002
01:43:54,806 --> 01:43:57,138
<i>Please. Please leave it on.</i>

1003
01:44:04,882 --> 01:44:06,782
I'm sorry.

1004
01:44:10,888 --> 01:44:14,346
<i>I just don't know exactly what it is you want.</i>

1005
01:44:15,927 --> 01:44:18,395
I don't want anything.

1006
01:44:20,365 --> 01:44:23,391
<i>Well, why'd you come here then?</i>

1007
01:44:32,110 --> 01:44:34,578
I -- I want to talk to you.

1008
01:44:55,166 --> 01:44:58,135
Is there something you want to tell me?

1009
01:45:01,172 --> 01:45:03,197
<i>No.</i>

1010
01:45:07,679 --> 01:45:10,648
You can tell me. I can keep a secret.

1011
01:45:19,857 --> 01:45:24,920
<i>This, uh--ls that all you do is just talk?</i>

1012
01:45:29,367 --> 01:45:31,392
Well, yeah.

1013
01:45:33,004 --> 01:45:35,199
Yeah, mostly.

1014
01:45:35,306 --> 01:45:37,206
And listen.

1015
01:45:41,379 --> 01:45:43,847
<i>What else do you do?</i>

1016
01:45:54,158 --> 01:45:57,025
<i>- Why are you laughing?</i>
- I'm sorry.

1017
01:46:02,166 --> 01:46:04,600
I'm sorry.

1018
01:46:04,702 --> 01:46:07,170
<i>So what else do you do?</i>

1019
01:46:09,173 --> 01:46:11,073
Nothin' really.

1020
01:46:13,911 --> 01:46:17,005
Oh, well, we're not allowed
to see the customers out here.

1021
01:46:18,950 --> 01:46:21,510
Where do you see them then?

1022
01:46:21,619 --> 01:46:23,587
Do you go home with them?

1023
01:46:24,989 --> 01:46:26,957
No, sir, we don't.

1024
01:46:29,327 --> 01:46:33,127
We're not allowed to have any
outside relationships with the customers.

1025
01:46:33,231 --> 01:46:36,200
Yeah, but you can really see 'em
if you want to, can't you?

1026
01:46:36,300 --> 01:46:39,269
I mean, you can go home with 'em
if you want to. All these places say that.

1027
01:46:39,370 --> 01:46:43,830
How much extra money do you make? How much --
How much money do you make on the side?

1028
01:46:55,386 --> 01:46:59,823
I'm sorry, sir. I think you'll maybe
want to talk to one of the other girls.

1029
01:46:59,924 --> 01:47:02,188
I'll see if I can find one for you.

1030
01:47:02,293 --> 01:47:04,761
No. No, no, no!

1031
01:47:04,862 --> 01:47:06,830
Please. Please.

1032
01:47:08,433 --> 01:47:10,401
Please don't go.

1033
01:47:15,006 --> 01:47:18,203
I just don't think
I'm the one you want to talk to.

1034
01:47:20,645 --> 01:47:23,011
Please.

1035
01:47:23,114 --> 01:47:25,412
Please don't go. I'm sorry.

1036
01:47:34,125 --> 01:47:36,650
All right.

1037
01:47:42,366 --> 01:47:46,769
I'm, um -- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1038
01:47:51,742 --> 01:47:54,734
That's okay.

1039
01:48:03,154 --> 01:48:05,145
<i>You know, I--</i>

1040
01:48:05,256 --> 01:48:08,714
<i>I know how hard it is to talk</i>
<i>to strangers sometimes.</i>

1041
01:48:14,065 --> 01:48:15,965
<i>Just relax.</i>

1042
01:48:17,468 --> 01:48:19,868
<i>Relax and tell me what's on your mind.</i>

1043
01:48:22,240 --> 01:48:24,140
I'll listen...

1044
01:48:26,244 --> 01:48:28,144
to you.

1045
01:48:32,683 --> 01:48:35,151
I don't mind listening.

1046
01:48:43,094 --> 01:48:45,722
I do it all the time.

1047
01:49:06,817 --> 01:49:09,012
She was there, wasn't she?

1048
01:49:47,558 --> 01:49:49,458
<i>What's that?</i>

1049
01:49:54,932 --> 01:49:56,832
A vacant lot.

1050
01:49:56,934 --> 01:50:01,564
<i>I bought that land when we were all together,</i>
<i>with your mom.</i>

1051
01:50:04,609 --> 01:50:07,578
I thought we might live there someday.

1052
01:50:09,981 --> 01:50:11,676
Where?

1053
01:50:11,782 --> 01:50:14,979
<i>Paris, Texas.</i>

1054
01:50:15,086 --> 01:50:16,986
Where's that?

1055
01:50:18,322 --> 01:50:20,984
It's close to the Red River.

1056
01:50:25,396 --> 01:50:27,762
<i>Do you like it?</i>

1057
01:50:27,865 --> 01:50:30,390
You mean we'd live on dirt?

1058
01:50:45,583 --> 01:50:48,552
Why do you drink that stuff?
It stinks.

1059
01:50:50,521 --> 01:50:53,979
- Wait a minute. Where are you going?
- To the truck.

1060
01:51:14,712 --> 01:51:16,703
Have another one?

1061
01:51:57,688 --> 01:51:59,588
Come on, Dad.

1062
01:52:25,349 --> 01:52:28,147
This is not a place to bring a fancy woman.

1063
01:52:31,255 --> 01:52:36,022
Would you say? If you had a fancy woman,
would you bring her in a place like this?

1064
01:52:36,127 --> 01:52:38,561
What's a fancy woman?

1065
01:52:55,412 --> 01:52:58,609
Oh! God.

1066
01:52:58,716 --> 01:53:00,877
My mother--

1067
01:53:02,253 --> 01:53:04,153
<i>Not your mother...</i>

1068
01:53:04,255 --> 01:53:06,917
but my mother...

1069
01:53:07,024 --> 01:53:09,584
was not a fancy woman.

1070
01:53:09,693 --> 01:53:12,059
She was --

1071
01:53:17,468 --> 01:53:22,064
She never wanted to be a fancy woman.
She never even pretended to be a fancy woman.

1072
01:53:22,173 --> 01:53:24,903
Then what was she?

1073
01:53:25,009 --> 01:53:27,534
<i>She was just plain.</i>

1074
01:53:29,814 --> 01:53:31,782
Just plain and good.

1075
01:53:31,882 --> 01:53:34,715
<i>She was very good.</i>

1076
01:53:34,819 --> 01:53:36,719
<i>But my daddy--</i>

1077
01:53:39,323 --> 01:53:42,190
See, my daddy had, uh --

1078
01:53:42,293 --> 01:53:44,284
He had this idea --

1079
01:53:44,395 --> 01:53:48,491
he had this idea in his head
that was kind of--

1080
01:53:48,599 --> 01:53:52,399
kind of-- kind of a sickness.

1081
01:53:52,503 --> 01:53:54,403
<i>What idea?</i>

1082
01:53:54,505 --> 01:53:56,939
He had this idea about her...

1083
01:53:57,041 --> 01:53:58,941
<i>and...</i>

1084
01:54:00,444 --> 01:54:03,140
<i>he looked at her...</i>

1085
01:54:03,247 --> 01:54:05,715
but he didn't see her.

1086
01:54:08,252 --> 01:54:11,881
<i>He--He saw this idea.</i>

1087
01:54:15,726 --> 01:54:19,594
And he told people that she was from Paris.

1088
01:54:21,265 --> 01:54:23,995
It was a big joke...

1089
01:54:24,101 --> 01:54:26,001
but he started telling everybody
all the time...

1090
01:54:26,103 --> 01:54:28,071
and finally it wasn't a joke anymore.
He st --

1091
01:54:31,575 --> 01:54:33,702
He started believing it.

1092
01:54:35,179 --> 01:54:38,307
And he actually believed it.

1093
01:54:41,619 --> 01:54:43,644
And she --

1094
01:54:43,754 --> 01:54:46,086
Oh, God.

1095
01:54:46,190 --> 01:54:48,988
She would get so embarrassed.

1096
01:54:50,794 --> 01:54:52,785
She --

1097
01:54:52,897 --> 01:54:55,195
She was so --

1098
01:54:57,401 --> 01:54:59,699
She was so shy.

1099
01:55:48,285 --> 01:55:50,253
<i>Vámonos, muchacho.</i>

1100
01:56:19,116 --> 01:56:21,016
Left, Dad.

1101
01:56:35,699 --> 01:56:37,997
Hunter, it's me.

1102
01:56:41,238 --> 01:56:44,696
I was afraid I'd never be able
to say the right words to you...

1103
01:56:44,808 --> 01:56:47,072
in person...

1104
01:56:47,177 --> 01:56:51,113
so I'm trying to do it like this.

1105
01:56:54,118 --> 01:56:57,178
When I first saw you this time...

1106
01:56:58,255 --> 01:57:00,155
at Walt's...

1107
01:57:01,492 --> 01:57:04,950
I was hoping for all kinds of things.

1108
01:57:06,897 --> 01:57:10,526
I was hoping to show you
that I was your father.

1109
01:57:12,669 --> 01:57:14,796
You showed me I was.

1110
01:57:18,342 --> 01:57:21,311
But the biggest thing I hoped for...

1111
01:57:23,514 --> 01:57:25,482
can't come true.

1112
01:57:27,851 --> 01:57:30,319
I know that now.

1113
01:57:32,022 --> 01:57:34,513
You belong together with your mother.

1114
01:57:36,860 --> 01:57:39,624
<i>You belong together with your mother.</i>

1115
01:57:41,265 --> 01:57:44,428
<i>It was me that tore you apart...</i>

1116
01:57:44,535 --> 01:57:47,993
<i>and I owe it to you to bring you back together.</i>

1117
01:57:49,473 --> 01:57:51,964
But I can't stay with you.

1118
01:57:52,076 --> 01:57:55,637
<i>I could never heal up what happened.</i>

1119
01:57:55,746 --> 01:57:59,182
That's just the way it is.

1120
01:57:59,283 --> 01:58:02,650
I can't even hardly remember what happened.

1121
01:58:02,753 --> 01:58:05,119
It's like a gap.

1122
01:58:05,222 --> 01:58:07,918
But it left me alone in a way that...

1123
01:58:08,025 --> 01:58:10,391
I haven't gotten over.

1124
01:58:10,494 --> 01:58:14,021
And right now, I'm afraid.

1125
01:58:15,766 --> 01:58:18,894
I'm afraid of walking away again.

1126
01:58:19,002 --> 01:58:21,470
I'm afraid of what I might find.

1127
01:58:23,006 --> 01:58:25,668
But I'm even more afraid of...

1128
01:58:25,776 --> 01:58:29,075
not facing this fear.

1129
01:58:29,179 --> 01:58:31,647
I love you, Hunter.

1130
01:58:32,816 --> 01:58:35,546
I love you more than my life.

1131
01:58:46,597 --> 01:58:48,497
Hey.

1132
01:58:48,599 --> 01:58:50,499
Hey.

1133
01:58:55,038 --> 01:58:57,734
Can I tell you something?

1134
01:58:59,309 --> 01:59:02,005
Sure. Anything you like.

1135
01:59:03,547 --> 01:59:05,447
It's kind of long.

1136
01:59:06,550 --> 01:59:08,848
I got plenty of time.

1137
01:59:32,276 --> 01:59:34,642
I knew these people.

1138
01:59:34,745 --> 01:59:36,645
What people?

1139
01:59:37,948 --> 01:59:39,916
These two people.

1140
01:59:45,022 --> 01:59:47,490
They were in love with each other.

1141
01:59:50,027 --> 01:59:52,723
The girl was... very young...

1142
01:59:52,829 --> 01:59:56,458
about 17 or 18, I guess.

1143
01:59:57,935 --> 02:00:01,393
And the guy was... quite a bit older.

1144
02:00:02,973 --> 02:00:06,067
He was kind of raggedy and wild.

1145
02:00:07,211 --> 02:00:09,645
And she was very beautiful, you know?

1146
02:00:11,682 --> 02:00:13,582
Yeah.

1147
02:00:13,684 --> 02:00:17,814
<i>And together they turned everything</i>
<i>into a kind of an adventure...</i>

1148
02:00:19,122 --> 02:00:21,989
<i>and she liked that.</i>

1149
02:00:22,092 --> 02:00:25,892
<i>Just an ordinary trip</i>
<i>down to the grocery store was...</i>

1150
02:00:25,996 --> 02:00:28,988
<i>full of adventure.</i>

1151
02:00:29,099 --> 02:00:32,865
And they were always laughing
at stupid things.

1152
02:00:32,970 --> 02:00:36,064
He liked to make her laugh.

1153
02:00:36,173 --> 02:00:38,141
And...

1154
02:00:39,710 --> 02:00:42,406
<i>they didn't much care for anything else...</i>

1155
02:00:42,512 --> 02:00:46,380
<i>because all they wanted to do</i>
<i>was be with each other.</i>

1156
02:00:48,185 --> 02:00:50,653
<i>They were always together.</i>

1157
02:00:50,754 --> 02:00:53,382
Sounds like they were very happy.

1158
02:00:53,490 --> 02:00:56,288
Yes, they were.

1159
02:00:56,393 --> 02:00:59,191
They were real happy.

1160
02:00:59,296 --> 02:01:02,595
And he -- he loved her more than...

1161
02:01:05,135 --> 02:01:07,262
he ever felt possible.

1162
02:01:10,340 --> 02:01:14,868
He couldn't stand being away from her,
uh, during the day when he went to work.

1163
02:01:20,317 --> 02:01:23,309
<i>So he'd quit...</i>

1164
02:01:23,420 --> 02:01:26,048
<i>just to be home with her.</i>

1165
02:01:26,156 --> 02:01:30,286
<i>Then he'd get another job</i>
<i>when the money ran out...</i>

1166
02:01:30,394 --> 02:01:32,919
<i>and then he'd quit again.</i>

1167
02:01:33,030 --> 02:01:35,828
<i>But pretty soon, she started to worry.</i>

1168
02:01:40,237 --> 02:01:43,035
- About what?
<i>- Money, I guess.</i>

1169
02:01:43,140 --> 02:01:45,040
<i>- Not having enough.</i>
- Mmm.

1170
02:01:45,142 --> 02:01:47,474
<i>Not knowing</i>
<i>when the next check was coming in.</i>

1171
02:01:49,646 --> 02:01:52,444
Yep, I know that feeling.

1172
02:01:52,549 --> 02:01:57,248
<i>So he started to get kind of torn inside.</i>

1173
02:02:00,957 --> 02:02:03,323
How do you mean?

1174
02:02:03,427 --> 02:02:06,487
<i>Well, he knew he had to work to support her...</i>

1175
02:02:06,596 --> 02:02:09,565
<i>but he couldn't stand</i>
<i>being away from her either.</i>

1176
02:02:11,268 --> 02:02:13,168
I see.

1177
02:02:13,270 --> 02:02:16,728
<i>And the more he was away from her,</i>
<i>the crazier he got...</i>

1178
02:02:17,908 --> 02:02:20,877
<i>except now he got really crazy.</i>

1179
02:02:24,348 --> 02:02:26,873
He started imagining all kinds of things.

1180
02:02:28,652 --> 02:02:30,552
Like what?

1181
02:02:32,222 --> 02:02:36,420
He started thinking
that she was seeing other men on the sly.

1182
02:02:37,794 --> 02:02:40,592
He'd come home from work
and accuse her of...

1183
02:02:40,697 --> 02:02:43,165
spending the day with somebody else.

1184
02:02:43,266 --> 02:02:45,962
He'd yell at her and break things in the trailer.

1185
02:02:48,505 --> 02:02:50,405
The trailer.

1186
02:02:55,579 --> 02:02:58,013
Yes.

1187
02:02:58,115 --> 02:03:00,583
They lived in a trailer home.

1188
02:03:15,365 --> 02:03:19,461
Excuse me, sir,
but were you in to visit me the other day?

1189
02:03:19,569 --> 02:03:21,867
I don't mean to pry.

1190
02:03:23,607 --> 02:03:26,167
No.

1191
02:03:26,276 --> 02:03:28,176
Oh.

1192
02:03:29,679 --> 02:03:33,308
I thought I recognized your voice for a minute.

1193
02:03:34,785 --> 02:03:37,754
No. Wasn't me.

1194
02:03:39,189 --> 02:03:41,089
Mm-hmm.

1195
02:03:43,160 --> 02:03:45,128
Please go on.

1196
02:03:47,564 --> 02:03:51,898
Anyway, he started to drink real bad...

1197
02:03:52,002 --> 02:03:55,130
and he'd stay out late to test her.

1198
02:03:56,973 --> 02:03:59,840
What do you mean "test her"?

1199
02:03:59,943 --> 02:04:02,571
To see if she'd get jealous.

1200
02:04:03,613 --> 02:04:06,241
Mm-hmm.

1201
02:04:08,051 --> 02:04:11,851
He wanted her to get jealous, but she didn't.

1202
02:04:11,955 --> 02:04:14,355
She just worried about him...

1203
02:04:14,458 --> 02:04:16,926
but that got him even madder.

1204
02:04:18,195 --> 02:04:20,561
Why?

1205
02:04:20,664 --> 02:04:22,996
Because...

1206
02:04:23,099 --> 02:04:26,500
he thought if she never got jealous of him
that she didn't really care about him.

1207
02:04:28,205 --> 02:04:32,574
<i>Jealousy was a sign of her love for him.</i>

1208
02:04:32,676 --> 02:04:35,110
<i>And then one night--</i>

1209
02:04:35,212 --> 02:04:39,308
<i>one night she told him that she was pregnant.</i>

1210
02:04:39,416 --> 02:04:42,283
<i>She was about three or four months pregnant...</i>

1211
02:04:42,385 --> 02:04:44,615
<i>and he didn't even know.</i>

1212
02:04:44,721 --> 02:04:47,918
<i>And then suddenly everything changed.</i>

1213
02:04:48,024 --> 02:04:51,983
<i>He stopped drinking and got a steady job.</i>

1214
02:04:52,095 --> 02:04:57,032
<i>He was convinced that she loved him now</i>
<i>because she was carrying his child.</i>

1215
02:04:57,133 --> 02:05:01,069
<i>And he was going to dedicate himself</i>
<i>to making a home for her.</i>

1216
02:05:02,272 --> 02:05:04,968
<i>But a funny thing started to happen.</i>

1217
02:05:05,075 --> 02:05:06,667
What?

1218
02:05:06,776 --> 02:05:09,176
<i>He didn't even notice it at first.</i>

1219
02:05:09,279 --> 02:05:11,873
<i>She started to change.</i>

1220
02:05:11,982 --> 02:05:16,885
<i>From the day the baby was born, she began</i>
<i>to get irritated with everything around her.</i>

1221
02:05:16,987 --> 02:05:19,717
<i>She got mad at everything.</i>

1222
02:05:19,823 --> 02:05:23,281
<i>Even the baby seemed to be an injustice to her.</i>

1223
02:05:23,393 --> 02:05:26,362
<i>He kept trying</i>
<i>to make everything all right for her--</i>

1224
02:05:26,463 --> 02:05:30,763
<i>buy her things,</i>
<i>take her out to dinner once a week.</i>

1225
02:05:30,867 --> 02:05:33,597
<i>But nothing seemed to satisfy her.</i>

1226
02:05:33,703 --> 02:05:37,366
<i>For two years,</i>
<i>he struggled to pull them back together...</i>

1227
02:05:37,474 --> 02:05:40,807
<i>like they were when they first met...</i>

1228
02:05:40,911 --> 02:05:45,371
<i>but finally he knew</i>
<i>that it was never gonna work out.</i>

1229
02:05:46,850 --> 02:05:48,943
<i>So he hit the bottle again.</i>

1230
02:05:49,052 --> 02:05:52,078
<i>But this time, it got mean.</i>

1231
02:05:52,188 --> 02:05:54,713
<i>This time, when he came home late at night...</i>

1232
02:05:54,824 --> 02:05:58,123
<i>she wasn't worried about him or jealous.</i>

1233
02:05:58,228 --> 02:06:00,560
<i>She was just enraged.</i>

1234
02:06:02,098 --> 02:06:06,535
<i>She accused him of holding her captive</i>
<i>by making her have a baby.</i>

1235
02:06:08,438 --> 02:06:11,407
<i>She told him that she dreamed about escaping.</i>

1236
02:06:11,508 --> 02:06:15,376
<i>That was all she dreamed about--escape.</i>

1237
02:06:15,478 --> 02:06:19,312
<i>She saw herself at night,</i>
<i>running naked down a highway...</i>

1238
02:06:19,416 --> 02:06:21,509
<i>running across fields...</i>

1239
02:06:21,618 --> 02:06:23,586
<i>running down riverbeds.</i>

1240
02:06:23,687 --> 02:06:25,587
<i>Always running.</i>

1241
02:06:25,689 --> 02:06:29,989
<i>And always, just when she was</i>
<i>about to get away, he'd be there.</i>

1242
02:06:30,093 --> 02:06:33,392
<i>He would stop her somehow.</i>

1243
02:06:33,496 --> 02:06:36,124
<i>He would just appear and stop her.</i>

1244
02:06:39,035 --> 02:06:43,563
<i>And when she told him these dreams,</i>
<i>he believed them.</i>

1245
02:06:43,673 --> 02:06:47,473
<i>He knew she had to be stopped,</i>
<i>or she'd leave him forever.</i>

1246
02:06:47,577 --> 02:06:50,239
<i>So he tied a cowbell to her ankle...</i>

1247
02:06:50,347 --> 02:06:54,306
<i>so he could hear at night</i>
<i>if she tried to get out of bed.</i>

1248
02:06:54,417 --> 02:06:58,285
<i>But she learned how to muffle the bell</i>
<i>by stuffing a sock into it...</i>

1249
02:06:58,388 --> 02:07:01,380
<i>and inching her way out of the bed...</i>

1250
02:07:01,491 --> 02:07:03,391
<i>and into the night.</i>

1251
02:07:04,628 --> 02:07:06,493
<i>He caught her one night</i>
<i>when the sock fell out...</i>

1252
02:07:06,596 --> 02:07:09,121
<i>and he heard her trying to run to the highway.</i>

1253
02:07:09,232 --> 02:07:11,860
<i>He caught her,</i>
<i>dragged her back to the trailer...</i>

1254
02:07:11,968 --> 02:07:14,994
<i>and tied her to the stove with his belt.</i>

1255
02:07:16,873 --> 02:07:21,503
<i>He just left her there and went back to bed...</i>

1256
02:07:21,611 --> 02:07:25,479
<i>and lay there, listening to her scream.</i>

1257
02:07:25,582 --> 02:07:29,814
<i>Then he listened to his son scream.</i>

1258
02:07:29,919 --> 02:07:32,387
<i>He was surprised at himself because...</i>

1259
02:07:32,489 --> 02:07:35,287
<i>he didn't feel anything anymore.</i>

1260
02:07:36,926 --> 02:07:39,895
<i>All he wanted to do was sleep.</i>

1261
02:07:41,831 --> 02:07:44,026
And for the first time...

1262
02:07:44,134 --> 02:07:46,898
he wished he were far away...

1263
02:07:50,040 --> 02:07:54,841
lost in a deep, vast country
where nobody knew him...

1264
02:07:54,944 --> 02:07:57,572
somewhere without language...

1265
02:07:57,681 --> 02:08:00,377
or streets.

1266
02:08:00,483 --> 02:08:04,442
And he dreamed about this place
without knowing its name.

1267
02:08:04,554 --> 02:08:07,887
And when he woke up, he was on fire.

1268
02:08:10,894 --> 02:08:14,853
There were blue flames
burning the sheets of his bed.

1269
02:08:14,964 --> 02:08:17,626
He ran through the flames...

1270
02:08:17,734 --> 02:08:21,226
toward the only two people he loved...

1271
02:08:21,337 --> 02:08:23,237
but they were gone.

1272
02:08:25,909 --> 02:08:29,868
<i>His arms were burning,</i>
<i>and he threw himself outside and--</i>

1273
02:08:31,614 --> 02:08:34,242
<i>and rolled on the wet ground.</i>

1274
02:08:36,519 --> 02:08:38,487
Then he ran.

1275
02:08:39,756 --> 02:08:42,224
He never looked back at the fire.

1276
02:08:44,794 --> 02:08:46,955
He just ran.

1277
02:08:52,869 --> 02:08:55,497
<i>He ran until the sun came up...</i>

1278
02:08:56,740 --> 02:08:59,834
<i>and he couldn't run any further.</i>

1279
02:09:01,044 --> 02:09:03,512
<i>Then when the sun went down...</i>

1280
02:09:03,613 --> 02:09:05,581
<i>he ran again.</i>

1281
02:09:11,488 --> 02:09:15,390
<i>For five days, he ran like this...</i>

1282
02:09:15,492 --> 02:09:18,325
<i>until every sign of man...</i>

1283
02:09:21,097 --> 02:09:23,065
<i>had disappeared.</i>

1284
02:09:34,177 --> 02:09:36,077
Travis.

1285
02:10:18,655 --> 02:10:21,886
If you turn the light off in there,
will you be able to see me?

1286
02:10:30,333 --> 02:10:32,301
I don't know.

1287
02:10:36,840 --> 02:10:38,808
I never tried.

1288
02:10:57,627 --> 02:10:59,754
Can you see me?

1289
02:11:01,297 --> 02:11:03,993
Yeah.

1290
02:11:04,100 --> 02:11:06,227
Do you recognize me?

1291
02:11:08,338 --> 02:11:10,238
Oh, Travis.

1292
02:11:17,714 --> 02:11:20,182
I brought Hunter with me.

1293
02:11:32,328 --> 02:11:34,626
Don't you want to see him?

1294
02:11:36,733 --> 02:11:38,633
Yeah.

1295
02:11:47,310 --> 02:11:51,804
I wanted to see him so bad
that I didn't even dare imagine him anymore.

1296
02:11:57,954 --> 02:12:00,752
Anne kept sendin' me pictures of him...

1297
02:12:03,760 --> 02:12:06,228
until I asked her to stop.

1298
02:12:12,468 --> 02:12:15,494
I couldn't stand the... pain...

1299
02:12:15,605 --> 02:12:18,574
of seeing him grow up and missin' it.

1300
02:12:27,483 --> 02:12:30,452
Why didn't you keep him with you, Jane?

1301
02:12:33,623 --> 02:12:35,591
I couldn't, Travis.

1302
02:12:39,762 --> 02:12:42,731
I didn't have what I knew he needed.

1303
02:12:49,405 --> 02:12:53,034
I didn't want to use him
to fill all my emptiness.

1304
02:12:58,448 --> 02:13:00,746
Well, he needs you now, Jane...

1305
02:13:00,850 --> 02:13:02,818
and he wants to see you.

1306
02:13:02,919 --> 02:13:04,887
He does?

1307
02:13:07,357 --> 02:13:09,257
Yes.

1308
02:13:13,429 --> 02:13:15,897
He's -- He's waiting for you.

1309
02:13:15,999 --> 02:13:17,899
Where?

1310
02:13:20,436 --> 02:13:22,904
Downtown...

1311
02:13:23,006 --> 02:13:24,974
in a hotel.

1312
02:13:26,876 --> 02:13:28,776
The Meridian.

1313
02:13:30,780 --> 02:13:32,680
Room 1520.

1314
02:13:37,620 --> 02:13:39,520
1520.

1315
02:13:40,656 --> 02:13:43,454
You're not going, are you?

1316
02:13:58,174 --> 02:14:00,642
I can't see you, Jane.

1317
02:14:02,545 --> 02:14:04,513
Don't go yet.

1318
02:14:08,885 --> 02:14:10,853
Don't go yet.

1319
02:14:29,138 --> 02:14:31,038
I --

1320
02:14:33,309 --> 02:14:36,938
I used to make up long speeches to you
after you left.

1321
02:14:42,018 --> 02:14:44,680
I used to talk to you all the time...

1322
02:14:44,787 --> 02:14:47,085
even though I was alone.

1323
02:14:50,460 --> 02:14:53,918
I walked around for months talking to you.

1324
02:14:58,034 --> 02:15:00,502
Now I don't know what to say.

1325
02:15:05,108 --> 02:15:08,077
It was easier when I just imagined you.

1326
02:15:16,018 --> 02:15:18,987
I even imagined you talking back to me.

1327
02:15:23,626 --> 02:15:26,527
We'd have long conversations...

1328
02:15:28,097 --> 02:15:30,065
the two of us.

1329
02:15:33,736 --> 02:15:36,204
It was almost like you were there.

1330
02:15:40,543 --> 02:15:42,511
I could hear you.

1331
02:15:42,612 --> 02:15:44,580
I could see you, smell you.

1332
02:15:46,682 --> 02:15:48,650
I could hear your voice.

1333
02:15:51,721 --> 02:15:54,349
Sometimes your voice would wake me up.

1334
02:15:57,226 --> 02:15:59,194
It would wake me up in the middle of the night...

1335
02:15:59,295 --> 02:16:01,525
just like you were there in the room with me.

1336
02:16:10,072 --> 02:16:11,972
Then...

1337
02:16:14,844 --> 02:16:16,812
it slowly faded.

1338
02:16:18,948 --> 02:16:21,416
I couldn't picture you anymore.

1339
02:16:25,054 --> 02:16:28,285
I tried to talk out loud to you like I used to...

1340
02:16:28,391 --> 02:16:30,859
but there was nothin' there.

1341
02:16:34,297 --> 02:16:36,629
I couldn't hear you.

1342
02:16:41,938 --> 02:16:43,838
Then...

1343
02:16:48,711 --> 02:16:50,679
I just gave up.

1344
02:16:57,153 --> 02:16:59,280
Everything stopped.

1345
02:17:01,090 --> 02:17:02,990
You...

1346
02:17:06,796 --> 02:17:08,923
just disappeared.

1347
02:17:15,104 --> 02:17:17,334
Now I'm working here.

1348
02:17:22,912 --> 02:17:25,710
I hear your voice all the time.

1349
02:17:30,052 --> 02:17:33,954
Every man...

1350
02:17:34,056 --> 02:17:36,251
has your voice.

1351
02:17:54,977 --> 02:17:58,435
I'll tell Hunter... that you're coming.

1352
02:18:03,419 --> 02:18:05,944
- Travis?
- What?

1353
02:18:09,792 --> 02:18:11,760
I'll be there.

1354
02:18:16,465 --> 02:18:18,365
Good.

1355
02:18:23,339 --> 02:18:25,239
Meridian Hotel.

1356
02:18:25,341 --> 02:18:27,241
Yeah.

1357
02:18:30,846 --> 02:18:34,543
Room 1520.

1358
02:19:43,419 --> 02:19:46,183
<i>Yeah!</i>

1359
02:19:46,288 --> 02:19:49,018
<i>"Why, you little"--</i>

1360
02:19:49,125 --> 02:19:52,117
<i>Yeah!</i>

1361
02:19:52,228 --> 02:19:56,028
<i>Yeah.</i>

1362
02:21:23,986 --> 02:21:26,477
Your hair, it's wet.

1363
02:21:35,564 --> 02:21:37,759
Oh!
